de.schlegel11.jfxanimation

Class JFXAnimationTemplate<N>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.schlegel11.jfxanimation.JFXAnimationTemplate<N>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JFXTemplateAction<N>, JFXTemplateBuilder<N>, JFXTemplateConfig<N>, JFXTemplateProcess<N>

    public class JFXAnimationTemplate<N>
extends Object
implements JFXTemplateConfig<N>, JFXTemplateBuilder<N>
    Class which represents a general JFXAnimationTemplate.
    This class is responsible for providing methods where it's possible to build a CSS like structured animation.
    Since:
    2018-09-18
    Author:
    Marcel Schlegel (schlegel11)

      • create

        public static <N> JFXTemplateProcess<N> create(Class<N> animationObjectType)
        Create a JFXTemplateProcess with a specific default animation type.
        The default animation objects with this type are set later in the JFXTemplateBuilder.build(Object) method.
        These objects are generally used in JFXTemplateAction.action(Function) methods.
        Type Parameters:
        N - the specific type.
        Parameters:
        animationObjectType - a specific animation object type.
        Returns:
        a JFXTemplateProcess instance.
